    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>About-Face: The Politics of CO2</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Robert W Albrecht letter says nuclear power is key to reducing carbon dioxide emissions in long run, but politicians are afraid to utter word (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''Mr. Bush Reverses Course'' (editorial, March 15):</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''Mr. Bush Reverses Course'' (editorial, March 15):</p>
        <p>The secret word is ''nuclear.'' If we want to reduce carbon dioxide emissions in the long run (the only thing that counts), we will ''go nuclear.'' But politicians, Republicans and Democrats alike, are afraid to utter the word.</p>
        <p>ROBERT W. ALBRECHT  Seattle, March 15, 2001</p>
        <p>The writer is an electrical engineering professor, University of Washington.</p>
      </block>
